revision.text:
'''Bowden Glacier''' ({{Coord|78|8|S|163|7|E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a [[glacier]] lying on the southeast flank of [[Salient Ridge]] that flows northeast to [[Blue Glacier (Antarctica)|Blue Glacier]], [[Victoria Land]]. It was named by the [[New Zealand Geographic Board]] in 1994 for [[Charles Bowden (politician)|Charles Bowden]], first chairman of the [[Ross Dependency Committee]] during [[Sir Edmund Hillary]]'s [[South Pole]] Expedition, part of the [[Commonwealth Trans-Antarctic Expedition]] in 1957. Bowden also served as a member of the [[Parliament of New Zealand]] until 1955.

