==O==

{{glossary}}
{{term|[[Ohm]]}}
{{defn|The SI derived unit of electrical resistance.}}
{{term|[[Ohm's law]]}}
{{defn|States that the current through a conductor between two points is directly proportional to the potential difference across the two points.}}
{{term|[[optical tweezers]]}}
{{defn|An [[optomechanical]] device used for the capture, analysis and manipulation of dielectric objects or particles, which operates via the application of force by the electric field of light.}}
{{term|[[optically detected magnetic resonance]]}}
{{defn|An optical technique for the initialisation and readout of {{gli|quantum spin}} in some crystal defects.}}
{{term|[[optics]]}}
{{defn|The branch of physics which involves the behaviour and properties of {{gli|light}}, including its interactions with matter and the construction of instruments that use or detect it. Optics usually describes the behaviour of visible, ultraviolet, and infrared light; however, because light is one of several forms of {{gli|electromagnetic radiation}}, other forms such as {{gli|X-ray|X-rays}}, microwaves, and radio waves exhibit similar properties.}}
{{glossaryend}}

