{{Infobox journal | title = Qualitative Inquiry | cover = Qualitative Inquiry.jpg | editor = Yvonna Lincoln, Norman K Denzin | discipline = [[Sociology]] | former_names = | abbreviation = Qual. Inq. | publisher = [[SAGE Publications]] | country = | frequency = 8/year | history = 1995-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 1.207 | impact-year = 2017 | website = http://www.sagepub.com/journals/Journal200797 | link1 = http://qix.sagepub.com/content/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://qix.sagepub.com/content/by/year | link2-name = Online archive | ISSN = 1077-8004 | eISSN = 1552-7565 | OCLC = 641771564 | LCCN = 95658119 | CODEN = QUINFS }} '''''Qualitative Inquiry''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that covers methodological issues raised by qualitative research in the [[social sciences]]. The journal's [[editors-in-chief]] are Yvonna Lincoln ([[Texas A&M University]]) and Norman K. Denzin ([[University of Illinois at Urbana–Champaign]]). It was established in 1995 and is currently published by [[SAGE Publications]].
== Abstracting and indexing == ''Qualitative Inquiry'' is abstracted and indexed in [[Scopus]] and the [[Social Sciences Citation Index]]. According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', its 2017 [[impact factor]] is 1.207, ranking it 44 out of 98 journals in the category "Social Sciences, Interdisciplinary".<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2017 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Social Sciences, Interdisciplinary |title=2017 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Social Sciences |accessdate=2017-06-30 |series=Web of Science |postscript=.}}</ref>
