{{Infobox journal | title = Qualitative Research | cover = Qualitative Research.jpg | editor = Bella Dicks, Karen Henwood, William Housley | discipline = [[Research Methods]] | former_names = | abbreviation = Qual. Res. | publisher = [[Sage Publications]] | country = | frequency = Bimonthly | history = 2001-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 2.951 | impact-year = 2017 | website = http://www.sagepub.com/journals/Journal201501/title | link1 = http://qrj.sagepub.com/content/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://qrj.sagepub.com/content/by/year | link2-name = Online archive | JSTOR = | OCLC = 47226463 | LCCN = 2009233391 | CODEN = | ISSN = 1468-7941 | eISSN = 1741-3109 }} '''''Qualitative Research''''' is a bimonthly [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering [[qualitative research]] methods in the fields of [[sociology]] and other [[social sciences]]. It was established in 2001 and is published by [[Sage Publications]]. The founding editors were [[Sara Delamont]] and P. Atkinson.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cardiff.ac.uk/people/view/38099-delamont-sara|title=Sara Delamont staff profile|publisher=Cardiff University|accessdate=28 March 2017}}</ref> The current [[editors-in-chief]] are Bella Dicks, Karen Henwood, and William Housley ([[Cardiff University]]).
== Abstracting and indexing == The journal is abstracted and indexed in [[Scopus]], and the [[Social Sciences Citation Index]]. According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', its 2017 [[impact factor]] was 2.951.<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2018 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Sociology |title=2017 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Clarivate Analytics]] |edition= Sciences |work=[[Web of Science]]}}</ref>
