{{hatlink|For ''SpaceNews'' (a daily news segment on Canadian television station Space), see its successor, ''[[InnerSPACE]]''.}} {{Notability|Web|date=May 2018}} {{Infobox Newspaper | logo = Space News logo.png | caption = | title = SpaceNews | type = Publication ([[news]]) | ceo = Greg Thomas | foundation = 1989 | language = English | country = [[United States]] | headquarters =[[Alexandria, Virginia]] | owner = Pocket Ventures, LLC. | categories = [[Space]] | website = {{URL|spacenews.com}} | ISSN = 1046-6940 }}
'''''SpaceNews''''' is a print and digital publication that covers business and political news in the [[space]] and [[satellite]] industry. ''SpaceNews'' provides news, commentary and analysis to an audience of government officials, politicians and executives within the space industry.<ref>{{cite web|title=SpaceNews|url=http://www.spacenews.com|website=SpaceNews|accessdate=13 June 2014}}</ref> ''SpaceNews'' details topics in civil, military and commercial [[Outer space|space]] and the satellite communications business.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pocket Ventures acquires Space News|url=http://www.steelpointcp.com/pocket-ventures-acquires-space-news/|website=Steelpoint Capital Partners LP|accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref>
''SpaceNews'' covers important news in North America, Europe, Asia, Africa, the Middle East and South America from [[NASA]], the [[European Space Agency|European Space Agency]]<nowiki/>, and [[private spaceflight]] firms such as [[Arianespace]], [[International Launch Services]], [[SpaceX]] and [[United Launch Alliance]]. The magazine regularly features profiles on relevant and important figures within the space industry. These profiles have featured numerous government leaders, corporate executives and other knowledgeable space experts, including NASA administrators [[Richard H. Truly|Richard Truly]], [[Daniel Goldin]], [[Sean O'Keefe|Sean O’Keefe]], [[Michael D. Griffin|Michael Griffin]] and [[Charles Bolden|Charles Boldin]]. <ref>{{cite web|title=Schafer Featured In SpaceNews|url=http://www.schafercorp.com/schafer-featured-spacenews/|website=Schafer Corp|accessdate=16 June 2014|date=2014-06-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Space News: Profile {{!}} U.S. Rep. Adam Schiff, Member, House Appropriations commerce, justice, science subcommittee|url=http://schiff.house.gov/articles-opeds/space-news-profile-us-rep-adam-schiff-member-house-appropriations-commerce-justice-science-subcommittee/|website=Congressman Adam Schiff|accessdate=16 June 2014}}</ref>
Founded in 1989, ''SpaceNews'' publishes its flagship magazine 20 times per year.<ref>{{cite web|title=Space News Magazine|url=http://www.mondotimes.com/2/topics/5/107/4394|website=Mondo Times|accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref> Brian Berger, a journalist who joined ''SpaceNews'' in 1989 to cover the NASA and reusable launch vehicle beats, was named editor-in-chief in January 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://spacenews.com/author/brian-berger/|title=Brian Berger, Author at SpaceNews.com|website=SpaceNews.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-03-16}}</ref>
''SpaceNews'' produces and publishes several electronic newsletters, including First Up, First Up Satcom, SN Military.Space and SpaceNews This Week.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://spacenews.com/Newsletters/|title=SpaceNews Newsletters - SpaceNews.com|work=SpaceNews.com|access-date=2018-03-16|language=en-US}}</ref>
''SpaceNews'' produces the official show daily of the [[Space Symposium]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://spacenews.com/spacenews-to-produce-official-and-only-show-dailies-for-33rd-space-symposium/|title=SpaceNews to produce official — and only — Show Dailies for 33rd Space Symposium - SpaceNews.com|date=2017-03-14|work=SpaceNews.com|access-date=2018-03-16|language=en-US}}</ref>, a civil, military and commercial space conference the [[Space Foundation]] holds annually in Colorado Springs, Colorado. The show daily is a tabloid-size print publication distributed to attendees during the conference. In 2018, ''SpaceNews'' began producing a print show daily for AIAA and Utah State University’s [[Conference on Small Satellites]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://spacenews.com/download-the-spacenews-smallsat-show-dailies/}}</ref>, held each August on the campus of [[Utah State University]] in Logan, Utah.
''SpaceNews'' was originally owned by the [[Army Times Publishing Company]], which was acquired by [[Gannett Company|Gannett]] in 1997.<ref>{{Cite web| title = Gannett Announces Preliminary Agreement to Acquire Army Times Publishing Co.| work = TEGNA| accessdate = 2018-09-01| date = 1997-06-13| url = http://www.tegna.com/gannett-announces-preliminary-agreement-to-acquire-army-times-publishing-co/}}</ref> In 2000, [[Space.com]] (later renamed Imaginova) acquired ''SpaceNews'' from Gannett.<ref>{{Cite web| title = GANNETT ACQUIRES EQUITY STAKE IN SPACE.com – Editor & Publisher| accessdate = 2018-09-01| url = https://www.editorandpublisher.com/news/gannett-acquires-equity-stake-in-space-com/}}</ref> ''SpaceNews'' is currently owned by Pocket Ventures, LLC., which acquired the publication from [[Imaginova]] in June 2012.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mickey|first1=Bill|title=Pocket Ventures Buys Weekly Magazine Space News|url=http://www.foliomag.com/2012/pocket-ventures-buys-weekly-magazine-space-news#.U5c-cyjrzd4|accessdate=13 June 2014|agency=Folio|date=9 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Wallace|first1=Alicia|title=Boulder-based Pocket Ventures Acquires Space News|url=http://www.dailycamera.com/business_old/ci_21006083/boulder-based-pocket-ventures-acquires-space-news|website=Daily Camera|accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Potter|first1=Beth|title=Investors pocket space-news publication|url=http://www.bcbr.com/article/20120705/NEWS/120709990/-1/events|website=Boulder County Business Report|accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref>
